p: Finally, arjunetin (9) ( m/z 695) was obtained as a white solid, identified on the basis of MS peaks and NMR spectral data ( Figure S9A,B) that corresponded to literature data [ 44]. The fragmentation ion m/z 487 ( Figure S9C) obtained from UPLC-MS/MS further confirms that the compound with m/z 695 is a glycoside of arjunic acid.
